                <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.00/270</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Ailing</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-19">November 19,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Hayter, First Secretary of the British Embassy, telephoned to me today with
                    further reference to the Lebanese situation. He said that the hour of 10 a.m.
                    Sunday, which had been set as the time limit for French action on the British
                    demands, had now been <pb facs="1050" n="1038" xml:id="pg_1038"/> postponed to
                    10 a.m. Monday. If by that hour the French have not acted, British martial law
                    will be declared in the Lebanon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paul</hi> H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Alling</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
